verbose_text: The Pantanal is an extremely dynamic system, with many natural and human induced changes happening simultaneously, and this makes it difficult to isolate the effects of individual factors, such as the effect of hydrelectric dams on the water level of Paraguay River [XREF_BIBR - XREF_BIBR] and alterations in sedimentation and manmade levees on the Taquari River [XREF_BIBR].
